<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 9:08PM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southeastern Le Flore
County through 945 PM CDT...
At 908 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 7 miles southwest of Heavener to 4 miles
northeast of Octavia. Movement was northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects
is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Big Cedar...                      Hodgen...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
